  "prompt": "What are best dating apps/sites in india?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, several dating apps and sites have gained popularity in India. The best choice may depend on your specific preferences, whether you're looking for casual dating, serious relationships, or something else. Here are some of the most popular dating apps and sites in India:\n\n1. **Tinder**: One of the most widely used dating apps in India, Tinder is known for its simple swipe-right-to-like and swipe-left-to-pass interface. It's suitable for casual dating as well as serious relationships.\n\n2. **Bumble**: This app empowers women by allowing only them to initiate conversations after a match is made. Bumble is used for dating, friendships, and even networking.\n\n3. **Happn**: Happn connects you with people you've crossed paths with in real life. It uses your location to show potential matches nearby.\n\n4. **OkCupid**: OkCupid uses a comprehensive questionnaire to help match users based on compatibility. It's popular for both casual and serious dating.\n\n5. **TrulyMadly**: An Indian dating app that focuses on verified profiles and encourages genuine connections. It uses trust scores to help ensure user safety.\n\n6. **Hinge**: Hinge is designed to be deleted, which means it focuses on fostering serious relationships. Users are encouraged to interact with profiles in a meaningful way.\n\n7. **Aisle**: Targeted towards those looking for serious relationships, Aisle is an invite-only app that caters to a more discerning audience.\n\n8. **Badoo**: This global dating app combines elements of social networking and dating, allowing users to meet new people in their area.\n\n9. **Coffee Meets Bagel**: This app focuses on quality over quantity, offering curated matches based on your profile and preferences.\n\n10. **EliteSingles**: This dating site is aimed at professionals and academics looking for serious relationships. It emphasizes compatibility based on lifestyle and values.\n\n11. **Shaadi.com**: Primarily a matrimonial site, Shaadi.com caters to those looking for arranged marriages but also has features for dating and serious relationships.\n\n12. **Jeevansathi**: Similar to Shaadi.com, Jeevansathi is focused on marriages but attracts a younger audience interested in dating too.\n\nWhen choosing a dating app or site, it\u2019s essential to consider factors such as your relationship goals, user demographics, and safety features. Always prioritize your safety and privacy while using these platforms.",
